# heartwall — Rodinia Benchmark (Baseline & PIM Variants)

## Benchmark Source

Rodinia Benchmark Suite 3.1  
===========================

Contact (for original code):  
Ke Wang: kw5na@virginia.edu  
Shuai Che: sc5nf@cs.virginia.edu  
Kevin Skadron: skadron@cs.virginia.edu

Rodinia wiki:  
http://lava.cs.virginia.edu/wiki/rodinia

---

## Build

Run:

```bash
make
```

This produces two executables:

- `heartwall_baseline.exe` — baseline code  
- `heartwall_pim.exe` — modified PIM code

> Note: The build will also compile the small AVI helper library located in `./AVI`.

---

## Input & Run

**Usage:**  
```
./heartwall_*.exe <inputfile> <num_frames> <num_threads>
```
- `inputfile`: path to an AVI file (a sample `test.avi` is provided).
- `num_frames`: number of frames to process.
- `num_threads`: number of OpenMP threads to use.

**Example:**

```bash
./heartwall_pim.exe test.avi 20 8
```

---

## PIM Output

The PIM variant (`heartwall_pim.exe`) generates:

- **`bbop_statistics.csv`** — execution time and energy consumption for each PIM system (bbop instruction), i.e., **SIMDRAM** and **Proteus**.
